   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>HYMN NO.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>179 9.9.6.6.6.4</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>"Almost persuaded," now to believe;</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>"Almost persuaded," Christ to receive;</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Seems now some soul to say,</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>"Go, Spirit, go Thy way,</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Some more convenient day</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>On Thee I'll call."</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>"Almost persuaded," come, come today;</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>"Almost persuaded," turn not away;</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Jesus invites you here,</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Angels are ling'ring near,</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Prayers rise from hearts so dear,</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>O wand'rer, come.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>"Almost persuaded," harvest is past!</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>"Almost persuaded," doom comes at last!</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>"Almost" cannot avail;</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>"Almost" is but to fail!</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Sad, sad, that bitter wail,</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>"Almost," but lost!</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Please be persuaded, He is so good;</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Please be persuaded, trust in His blood;</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Jesus forgives your sins,</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>All vileness He can cleanse;</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>His death your only means,</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Open your heart.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Now be persuaded; please, sinner, come.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Now be persuaded, make Christ your home.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Jesus is calling you,</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Yield, all you need to do;</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Blessing will come anew,</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Believe Him now.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Stanzas 1 through 3 written by P. P. Bliss.</S>
